Section3.Para:
Odum et al. (1960) proposed that the species per thousand individuals can be used as an index of diversity which is basically an evenness and is a very reliable index. It is calculated as




$$ \begin{array}{llll}\mathrm{ Odum}\mathrm{ s}\;\mathrm{in}\mathrm{ dex}\cr=\frac{{\mathrm{ No}.\;\mathrm{ of}\;\mathrm{total}\;\mathrm{ species}\;\mathrm{ in}\;\mathrm{ the}\;\mathrm{
sample}}}{{\mathrm{ No}.\;\mathrm{ of}\;\mathrm{ in}\mathrm{dividuals}\;\mathrm{ of}\;\mathrm{ all}\;\mathrm{ species}.}}\times 1,000. \end{array}$$
